entry.title: Big Idea 5.5 Legal and Ethical Concerns

link.title: Big Idea 5.5 Legal and Ethical Concerns

entry.summary: When you create a GitHub repository it requests a license type. Review the license types in relationship to this Tech Talk and make some notes in your personal blog. The type of license that Github offers when I looked at my repository was the Apache License 2.0. I researched what type of license it was and found that it is a type of open source, permissive software license. It says it allows commercial and private use, but their is trade mark use limitations. I think mine is an Open Source GPL License because this means the Github project must be public, which it is.
